        "name": "Lux No. 5",
        "description": "This is the tension you feel just before something breaks, or becomes something new.\nA harmonic interval of 7:5, expressed as light and gravity, it loops in on itself with impossible precision.\nThe form is taut. Bound. Like a rope caught mid-unravel.\nEach stroke is balance under pressure.\nA tritone in motion.",
